[[Dimension Films]].<ref name=\"vty\">{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/mandy-moore-shark-tale-47-meters-down-weinsteins-1201822542/|title=Mandy Moore's Shark Tale '47 Meters Down' Bought From Weinsteins|last=McNary|first=Dave|date=25 July 2016|work=Variety|accessdate=3 October 2017}}</ref> At the 2017 [[Toronto Film Festival]], Entertainment Studios also bought ''[[Chappaquiddick (film)|Chappaquiddick]]'', ''[[Replicas (film)|Replicas]]'', and ''[[Hostiles (film)|Hostiles]]''.<ref name=\"dl\">{{cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2017/10/hostiles-christian-bale-byron-allen-entertainment-studios-scott-cooper-rosamund-pike-ken-kao-oscar-season-launch-1202181081/|title=Byron Allen's Entertainment Studios Hostiles; Christian Bale-Starrer Gets Oscar Season Berth|last=Fleming|first=Mike|date=October 3, 2017|work=Deadline|accessdate=October 4, 2017}}</ref> Entertainment Studios aimed to distribute at least 18 films in 2018.<ref name=\"HostilesInterview\" /> In January 2018, on his film distribution model, Allen stated:\n\n{{quote|We're chasing the studio crumbs. They don't want movies that do $40 million to $60 million. We totally will be good with those numbers, and that is what we're pursuing. Our thing is we are really big on slow roll-outs and small releases. Our philosophy &mdash; we believe in wide releases. We like to have movies that are 1,500-4,000 screens and we are chasing what the studios don't want. They're chasing much bigger. And we're going to take their crumbs and make a gourmet meal. And then eventually we'll move on to chasing more than their crumbs. But today we're chasing the crumbs.<ref name=\"HostilesInterview\"/>}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year !! Release Date !! Film title !! Director !! Gross<ref>{{cite web |title=Entertainment Studios All Time Box Office Results |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/studio/chart/?yr=&view=company&view2=allmovies&studio=entertainmentstudios.htm&sort=open&order=ASC&p=.htm |website=BoxOfficeMojo.com |publisher=IMDb.com, Inc |accessdate=6 June 2018 |language=en}}</ref> !! Ref\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2017 || June 16, 2017 ||''[[47 Meters Down]]'' || [[Johannes Roberts]] || $44.3 million || <ref name=vty/>\n|-\n| September 22, 2017 || ''[[Friend Request]]'' || [[Simon Verhoeven]] || $3.7 million || <ref>{{cite news|last=Busch|first=Anita|title=Freestyle Releasing Gets 'Friend Request'|url=http://deadline.com/2016/01/friend-request-movie-acquisition-freestyle-releasing-byron-allen-1201683226/|accessdate=October 7, 2017|work=Deadline|date=January 14, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 22, 2017 || ''[[Hostiles (film)|Hostiles]]'' || [[Scott Cooper (director)|Scott Cooper]] || $40.9 million || <ref name=dl/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2018 || March 9, 2018 || ''[[The Hurricane Heist]]'' || [[Rob Cohen]]  || $15.8 million || <ref>{{cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2017/07/rob-cohen-the-hurricane-heist-byron-allen-entertainment-studios-motion-pictures-1202130540/|title=Rob Cohen's 'The Hurricane Heist' Acquired By Entertainment Studios|last=Ramos|first=Dino-Day|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=July 17, 2017|accessdate=October 4, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 6, 2018 || ''[[Chappaquiddick (film)|Chappaquiddick]]'' || [[John Curran (director)|John Curran]] || $18 million || <ref name=dl0>{{cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2017/09/chappaquiddick-ted-kennedy-movie-byron-allen-entertainment-studios-toronto-film-festival-deal-1202164260/|title=Ted Kennedy Scandal Film 'Chappaquiddick' Lands $20M Commitment From Byron Allen At Toronto|last=Busch|first=Anita|last2=Fleming|first2=Mike|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=September 8, 2017|accessdate=March 25, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=6|2019 || January 11, 2019 || ''[[Replicas (film)|Replicas]]'' || [[Jeffrey Nachmanoff]] || $8.1 million || <ref>{{cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2017/09/keanu-reeves-replicas-byron-allen-toronto-film-festival-sale-entertainment-studios-4-million-dollars-1202164154/|ti