sensor, [[Autofocus#Phase detection|PDAF]], [[Image stabilization#Optical image stabilization|OIS]], 3x optical zoom, Dual-LED flash, panorama, HDR, 8K@24/30fps, 4K@30/60fps, 1080p@30/60/120/240/960fps\n|front_camera='''K30/K30 5G/Poco X2''': Dual: 20 [[megapixel|MP]], (f/2.2, 27mm, 1/3.4\", 0.8\u00b5m), + 2MP depth sensor, (f/2.4, 1/5\", 1.75\u00b5m), HDR, 1080p@30fps<br>'''K30 Pro & K30 Pro Zoom''': 20 [[megapixel|MP]], (1/3.4\", 0.8\u00b5m), HDR, 1080p@30fps\n|memory= 6 or {{val|8|ul=Gigabyte{{!}}GB}} [[Random Access Memory|RAM]]<br>'''K30 Pro Zoom only''': 8 or 12 GB RAM\n|storage='''K30/K30 5G/Poco X2''': 64 [[Gigabyte|GB]], 128 [[Gigabyte|GB]] or 256 [[Gigabyte|GB]]<br>'''K30 Pro''': 128 [[Gigabyte|GB]] or 256 [[Gigabyte|GB]]<br>'''K30 Pro Zoom''': 128 [[Gigabyte|GB]], 256 or 512 [[Gigabyte|GB]]\n|memory_card='''K30/K30 5G/Poco X2''': [[microSD]], up to 256 GB<br>'''K30 Pro & K30 Pro Zoom''': None\n|connectivity=[[2G]], [[3G]], [[4G]], [[4G LTE]], [[5G]], Wi-Fi 802.11a/b/g/n/ac (2.4 & 5GHz), dual-band, WiFi Direct, DLNA, hotspot\n[[Bluetooth]] V5, [[A2DP]], Low-energy, [[aptX|aptX-HD]]\n|slogan=\n|website=\n}}\n\nThe '''Redmi K30/K30 5G'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techradar.com/in/news/xiaomi-redmi-k30-launched-in-china-to-become-the-cheapest-5g-smartphone|title=Xiaomi Redmi K30 launched in China to become the cheapest 5G smartphone|work=[[TechRadar]] India|last=Jhaveri|first=Aakash|date=10 December 2019|accessdate=10 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tomsguide.com/news/5g-phones-too-expensive-for-you-then-check-out-the-redmi-k30|title=5G phones too expensive for you? Then check out the Redmi K30|work=[[Tom's Hardware|Tom's Guide]]|last=Priday|first=Richard|date=10 December 2019|accessdate=10 December 2019}}</ref> and '''Redmi K30 Pro/K30 Pro Zoom'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/3/24/21192116/redmi-k30-pro-announced-specs-price-china-india-xiaomi|title=The Redmi K30 Pro is Xiaomi\u2019s new price-performance champion|work=[[The Verge]]|last=Byford|first=Sam|date=24 March 2020|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2020-03-24-xiaomi-redmi-k30-snapdragon-865-5g.html|title=Xiaomi's Redmi K30 Pro touts flagship specs at a mid-range price|work=[[Engadget]]|last=Dent|first=Steve|date=24 March 2020|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref> are [[Android (operating system)|Android-based]] [[smartphone]]s manufactured by [[Xiaomi]] and marketed under its [[Redmi]] sub-brand. A rebranded version of the K30 was later announced for India as the '''Poco X2'''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/2/4/21122022/xiaomi-poco-x2-announced-price-specs-realme-redmi-k30|title=Xiaomi spin-off Poco returns with the 120Hz X2 for $225|work=[[The Verge]]|last=Byford|first=Sam|date=4 February 2020|accessdate=4 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Specifications==\n===Design===\nThe devices use an anodized aluminum frame and [[Gorilla Glass]] on the front and back. The power button is recessed on the K30, K30 5G and Poco X2, while the K30 Pro and K30 Pro Zoom have a red accent instead. The K30, K30 5G and Poco X2 have dual front-facing cameras housed in a pill-shaped cutout, resembling the [[Samsung Galaxy S10|Galaxy S10+]], while the K30 Pro and K30 Pro Zoom retain the pop-up camera from the K20. At the rear, the camera protrusion is a single unit with a dual-LED flash below surrounded by a circular accent. The K30, K30 5G and Poco X2 have an oval module, while the K30 Pro and K30 Pro Zoom have a circular module. The K30, K30 5G and Poco X2 launched in (Phoenix) Red, (Matrix) Purple and (Atlantis) Blue, with an additional White finish available on the 5G version; the K30 Pro and K30 Pro Zoom will launch in Grey, Purple, White and Blue. Branding varies between devices, with the K30 and K30 5G having a vertically oriented Redmi logo, the K30 Pro and K30 Pro Zoom having a horizontally oriented Redmi logo, and the Poco X2 having a horizontally oriented Poco logo.\n\n===Hardware & Software===\nThe primary camera has been upgraded from a 48 MP sensor to a 64 MP sensor on all variants, while the telephoto lens is exclusive to the K30 Pro Zoom along with optical image stabilization on the wide lens, with other variants having a macro camera. The camera array on the K30, K30 5G and Poco X2 consists of a 64 MP wide sensor, an 8 MP ultrawide sensor, a 2 MP dedicated macro camera and a 2 MP depth sensor. On the K30 Pro & K30 Pro Zoom, the ultrawide sensor's resolution is 13 MP, however the resolution of the wide sensor and depth sensor remain the same. The K30 Pro has a 5 MP macro camera, while the K30 Pro Zoom has an 8 MP telephoto lens with 3x optical zoom; the K30 Pro Zoom also has OIS on the primary lens. The selfie camera's resolution is still 20 MP, and it is joined by a 2 MP depth sensor on the K30, K30 5G and Poco X2. At the front, the display itself is larger than the K20's at 6.67\" (169.4mm) and has a wider 20:9 [[Display aspect ratio|aspect ratio]] with a 120Hz [[refresh rate]] and HDR10 support. However, the screen is an LCD panel as opposed to the AMOLED panel of the K20 and K20 Pro, and as a result the fingerprint sensor is located on the side rather than an in-display optical unit. The K30 Pro and K30 Pro Zoom use an AMOLED display with an optical sensor and HDR10+ support, but only have a 60\u00a0Hz refresh rate. The K30, K30 5G and Poco X2 are powered by Qualcomm Snapdragon 700 series SoCs, with the K30 retaining the K20's Snapdragon 730G and Adreno 618 while the K30 5G receives the newer Snapdragon 765G and Adreno 620. The K30 Pro and K30 Pro Zoom use the flagship Snapdragon 865 and Adreno 650. Storage and RAM options have been carried over from the K20 (64, 128 or 256 GB of UFS 2.1 storage and 6 or 8 GB of RAM), although [[microSD]] card expansion is now supported up to 256 GB on the K30, K30 5G and Poco X2. The K30 Pro & K30 Pro Zoom have either 128 or 256 GB of storage and 6 or 8 GB of RAM with an additional 12 GB RAM/512 GB UFS variant on the K30 Pro Zoom; the 128 GB/6 GB K30 Pro model has UFS 3.0 while other models have UFS 3.1.The battery is 4500mAh on the K30, K30 5G and Poco X2, and 4700mAh on the K30 Pro & K30 Pro Zoom. Fast charging is supported for all devices; the K30 & Poco X2 support up to 27W, the K30 5G supports up to 30W, and the K30 Pro & K30 Pro Zoom support up to 33W. All devices are pre-installed with [[MIUI]] 11, which is based on [[Android 10]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Android smartphones}}\n{{Xiaomi}}\n\n[[Category:Smartphones]]\n[[Category:Xiaomi]]\n[[Category:Mobile phones introduced in 2019]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Smartphone manufactured by Xiaomi}}\n{{Infobox mobile phone|name=Redmi K30<br>Redmi K30 5G<br>Redmi K30 Pro<br>Redmi K30 Pro Zoom<br>Poco X2\n| logo=\n| image = Redmi K30 front.jpg\n| caption =\n| codename = \n| manufacturer=[[Xiaomi]]\n| series=[[Redmi]]\n| released='''K30''': {{start date and age|df=yes|2019|12|12}}<br>'''K30 5G''': {{start date and age|df=yes|2020|01|07}}<br>'''Poco X2''': {{start date and age|df=yes|2020|02|11}}<br>'''K30 Pro''': {{start date and age|df=yes|2020|03|27}}<br>'''K30 Pro Zoom''': {{start date and age|df=yes|2020|04|04}}\n| predecessor=[[Redmi K20]]\n| successor=\n| type=[[Slate phone|Touchscreen]] [[smartphone]]\n| form=[[Slate phone|Slate]]\n| size= '''K30/K30 5G/Poco X2''': <br>{{convert|165.3 x 76.6 x 8.8|mm|in|abbr=on}} <br /> '''K30 Pro & K30 Pro Zoom''': <br>{{convert|163.3 x 75.4 x 8.9|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n| weight='''K30/K30 5G/Poco X2''': <br>{{convert|208|g|oz|abbr=on}} <br />'''K30 Pro/K30 Pro Zoom''': <br>{{convert|218|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n|os=[[MIUI|MIUI 11]] based on [[Android 10]]\n|compatible networks=\n|soc='''K30 & Poco X2''': [[Qualcomm]] SM7150-AB [[List of Qualcomm Snapdragon systems-on-chip#Snapdragon 700 series|Snapdragon 730G]]<br>'''K30 5G''': [[Qualcomm]] SM7250-AB [[List of Qualcomm Snapdragon systems-on-chip#Snapdragon 700 series|Snapdragon 765G]] <br> '''K30 Pro & K30 Pro